{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The generated reply references specific points from the incoming email rather than producing a generic response.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real LLM output quality and variability (LLM-DEP). A mocked model or template stub can pass while still missing the real failure (generic, non-grounded replies), so lower-level tests can hide it (MOCK-HIDE).","test_description":"Run the drafting step against a real model on a fixed set of realistic email threads; assert the draft includes thread-specific anchors (e.g., key entities/actions from the thread) above a grounding threshold, and fail when outputs are generic across distinct inputs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The factual consistency check flags claims in the draft that contradict entries in the knowledge base.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Contradiction detection is typically semantic and model-judgment dependent (LLM-DEP). Pure in-process mocks can miss real false negatives/positives on nuanced contradictions (MOCK-MISS, MOCK-HIDE).","test_description":"Use real contradiction cases (draft claim vs KB fact) and run the factual-check component with the production model/settings; verify contradictory claims are flagged and non-contradictory controls are not, over repeated runs to capture model variance.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.65,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When the knowledge base has no relevant entries, the draft includes a disclaimer rather than fabricating facts.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The failure boundary is model behavior under missing context: hallucination vs safe disclaimer (LLM-DEP). Mocked generation can trivially return a disclaimer and hide real fabrication risk (MOCK-HIDE).","test_description":"With empty/irrelevant KB context and real incoming threads, run generation using the real model; assert presence of required disclaimer language and absence of unsupported factual assertions in the draft.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The approval workflow blocks sending until the user explicitly approves — no draft is sent automatically.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a local orchestration/state-handoff boundary (drafting -> approval state -> sender). A unit test of one function may miss wiring bugs between modules/queues/state transitions (MOCK-MISS). No real network/OS dependency is required to catch the core failure.","test_description":"Execute the local pipeline with a test mail-sender adapter and persistent state: generate + fact-check + present draft, then verify send is not invoked before explicit approval and is invoked only after approval event.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full sequence — read thread, generate draft, check facts, present for approval — works end-to-end for a real email thread.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This behavior explicitly spans multiple sequential stages and includes model-dependent steps (MULTI-STEP + LLM-DEP). End-to-end correctness can fail only when all real stages interact, which lower isolated levels can miss.","test_description":"Run a production-like end-to-end scenario on a real email thread fixture/source: ingest thread, generate draft with real model, run factual check, present approval UI/state, and verify final send remains blocked pending approval. Validate outputs and transitions at each stage.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.75}}]}
